SIMPLE: rosaceous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rosaceous
<hw>Ro*sa"ceous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>rosaceus</ets>, fr. <ets>rosa</ets> rose.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to a natural order
of plants (<ord>Rosaceae</ord>) of which the rose is the type. It
includes also the plums and cherries, meadowsweet, brambles, the
strawberry, the hawthorn, applies, pears, service trees, and
quinces.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Like a rose in shape or appearance;
<as>as, a <ex>rosaceous</ex> corolla</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of a pure purpish pink color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rosacic</ent>⟦br⟧
